BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Paying For It
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T190000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T190000
UID:shopify-8210063753260@cicadacinema.com
DESCRIPTION:$8.00 - Tickets for the 7 PM screening of PAYING FOR IT 2025 • Canada • 85 minutes • dir. Sook-Yin Lee Thursday\, March 26th at Backspace Gallery ( 112 W 6th St ) $ 8 | All Ages Showtime: 7pm TRAILER Synopsis : Based on the acclaimed autobiographical graphic novel of the same name\, Paying For It depicts the breakdown of renowned Canadian underground cartoonist Chester Brown's (Ed the Happy Clown\, Louis Riel\, Yummy Fur) last traditional relationship with Sook-Yin Lee\, who coincidentally also directed this film adaption. As their relationship falls apart after a dissatisfying attempt to open it by Sook-Yin\, Chester abandons all pretense and begins a life divorced from romantic relationships\, choosing instead to exclusively patronize sex workers going forward. Paying For It is essential viewing for fans of underground comics and independent cinema\, showing how an unconventional adaptation of an already unconventional work can end up as a very compelling picture that displays the nuances of the human condition and asks you to question the status quo. Cicada is pleased to present this indie gem at Backspace Gallery! Sponsored by: Bloomington Rentals and Realty
LOCATION:Backspace Gallery
URL:https://cicadacinema.com/products/paying-for-it-march-26-backspace-gallery-7pm
X-SOURCE:Cicada Cinema
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:http://cicadacinema.com/cdn/shop/files/PayingforItPoster1_8.5x11.png?v=1772917528
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pillion
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260422T200000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260422T200000
UID:shopify-8208657940524@cicadacinema.com
DESCRIPTION:$8.00 - Tickets for the 8 PM screening of PILLION 2026 • UK • 107 minutes • dir. Harry Lighton Wednesday\, April 22nd at The Back Door (207 S College Ave) $8 | 21+ Showtime: 8 pm TRAILER Synopsis : In his unorthodox queer romance\, first-time feature director Harry Lighton has fashioned something highly improbable: a film about a sadomasochistic relationship that is both transgressive and disarming. Harry Melling plays the mild Colin\, whose gayness is happily accepted by his parents (Lesley Sharp and Douglas Hodge) and who is most extroverted when singing in a barbershop quartet. When this sweet-natured square catches the eye of strapping\, leather-clad biker Ray (Alexander Skarsgård) at the local pub\, he finds himself entering a submissive role—both domestic and erotic—for the inscrutable beauty who brings him both satisfaction and confusion\, pain and pleasure. As their affair continues\, Colin must decide what he wants and needs—and who he really is. Comic without ever descending into judgment of its characters\, Pillion is a beguiling inquiry into the social and sexual performances of masculinity\, featuring fearless work from Melling and Skarsgård.
LOCATION:Back Door
URL:https://cicadacinema.com/products/pillion-april-22-back-door-8pm
X-SOURCE:Cicada Cinema
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:http://cicadacinema.com/cdn/shop/files/Pillion.Poster1_8.5x11.png?v=1772755990
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Society
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T190000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T190000
UID:shopify-8208655810604@cicadacinema.com
DESCRIPTION:$8.00 - Tickets for the 7 PM screening of SOCIETY 1989 • USA • 99 minutes • dir. Brian Yuzna Thursday\, April 16th at The Orbit Room (107 N College) $8 dollars | 18+ Showtime: 7pm T RAILER Synopsis : After producing Re-Animator \, Brian Yuzna turned his hand to directing with SOCIETY —one of the ickiest\, most original body horror shockers of all time. Teenager Bill Whitney has always felt like the odd one out in his wealthy\, upper-class Beverly Hills family. But his sense of alienation takes a sinister turn when he hears an audio recording of his sister’s coming-out party\, which seems to implicate his family in a bizarre\, ritualistic orgy. Packing stomach-churning grue courtesy Screaming Mad George ( A Nightmare on Elm Street 4 ) and thought-provoking social commentary in equal measure\, SOCIETY is a biting satire that culminates in the most gag-inducing “climax” in all of horror history. *Cicada Cinema is dedicated to curating a wide variety of films while ensuring a safe and inclusive moviegoing experience for all. Our mission to program underrepresented films can lead to screening films that may contain uncomfortable or otherwise insensitive imagery and content. We encourage you to research the films we program beforehand to determine if they could be upsetting to you. Please feel free to contact us for guidance on any film you may have questions about.
LOCATION:Orbit Room
URL:https://cicadacinema.com/products/society-april-16-orbit-room-7pm
X-SOURCE:Cicada Cinema
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:http://cicadacinema.com/cdn/shop/files/Societyposter3_8.5x11.png?v=1772755350
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Moment
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T200000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T200000
UID:shopify-8208652533804@cicadacinema.com
DESCRIPTION:$8.00 - Tickets for the 8 PM screening of THE MOMENT 2025 • USA • 103 minutes • dir. Aidan Zamiri Wednesday\, April 1st at The Back Door (207 S College Ave) $8 | 21+ Showtime: 8 pm TRAILER Synopsis : Channeling both This is Spinal Tap (1984) and Spice World (1997)\, Charli XCX's The Moment is a playful\, hilarious\, self-critical mockumentary about the iconic pop star and the price of fame. Co-starring Alexander Skarsgård and Hailey Gates\, as well as numerous cameos\, Charli XCX plays a version of herself as she embarks on a worldwide tour in support of the album brat\, navigating studio pressure\, corporate sponsorship\, and fan expectations. Can she survive The Moment with her cultural legacy intact? Find out with a very special April Fool's Day screening\, Wednesday\, April 1\, at the Back Door! (we promise this is not a prank)
LOCATION:Back Door
URL:https://cicadacinema.com/products/the-moment-april-1-back-door-8pm
