BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:SIRAT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T200000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T200000
UID:shopify-8195744432172@cicadacinema.com
DESCRIPTION:$0.00 - Tickets for the 8 PM screening of SIRAT 2025 • Morocco\, France • 115 minutes • dir. Oliver Laxe Saturday\, March 28th at Upland Wood Shop (354 W 11th St) FREE\, but ticketed | All Ages Showtime: 8pm *Sponsored by IU Arts &amp\; Humanities Council as part of Granfalloon 2026. More info at grafalloon.indiana.edu . TRAILER Synopsis : Sirāt follows Luis (Sergi López)\, a father on a mission to find his missing daughter who was last spotted at a rave in the Moroccan desert. With his son and their dog in tow\, the group find themselves immersed in desert rave culture and have to contend with the brutal landscape and hostile military presence in the region\, but not without some help\, cautious as it may be\, from a close-knit group of raver friends. As they venture deeper into the burning wilderness\, the journey forces them to confront their own limits. Sirāt is a powerful film\, bolstered by a powerful soundtrack by Kangding Ray and led by an uncompromising directorial effort by Oliver Laxe. The Cicada crew saw this one at Heartland International Film Festival last year and we've been working hard to bring this one to Bloomington\, so we couldn't be happier to deliver this one free of charge in a fantastic venue\, the Upland Wood Shop free of charge with support by Granfalloon.
LOCATION:Upland Wood Shop
URL:https://cicadacinema.com/products/sirat-march-28-upland-wood-shop-8pm
X-SOURCE:Cicada Cinema
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:http://cicadacinema.com/cdn/shop/files/SiratPoster2_8.5x11.png?v=1771787220
END:VEVENT
